  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: R5_WriteRecipe
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - You've come far, dear.
  - Every recipe you've learned until now has been preparing you for this one.
  - The Moonheart Elixir was created by the first Moonwardens to restore weakened
    magical lands.
  - It is not made from raw ingredients alone.
  - Instead, it combines completed brews, each carrying a different aspect of restoration.
  - As always, the first step is lighting the fire under the cauldron.
  - Even ancient magic requires a stable foundation.
  - The Moondrop Tonic restores vitality.
  - The Emberroot Brew restores strength and endurance.
  - The Moonbloom Elixir nurtures growth.
  - And the Swiftstep Draught carries adaptability and motion.
  - Healing. Strength. Growth. Adaptation.
  - The magical world cannot survive through one kind of magic alone.
  - Balance is what allows it to endure.
  - Now... let us see if the meadow still remembers.
  - Remember the sequence carefully.
  - First, light the fire under the cauldron.
  - Then add the Moondrop Tonic, Emberroot Brew, Moonbloom Elixir, and finally the
    Swiftstep Draught.
  - You did it...
  - For the first time in many years, the magic finally stands a chance....again.
